item.title: Involved
item.description: There are many ways to get involved. First, follow Michelle’s Facebook page. There you can find information about upcoming events, request a yard sign, or volunteer to host a meet and greet. A donation to the campaign can also be made here. Feel free to send a message via Facebook or to michelle4sachse@gmail.com for more information, or if you have another way to be involved.

item.title: About Michelle
item.description: Michelle and her family have called Sachse home since 1999. Prior to running for city council, Michelle served as a member and chairwoman of Sachse Zoning Board of Adjustments. She currently serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the Sachse Economic Development Corporation. Michelle has also served in the Collin County Medical Reserve Corps for several years. Michelle and her husband, Evan, are the parents of four children - one a current student and three graduates of Wylie High School.
